   <narrative xml:lang="EN">216818_South Kordofan IFA FY21</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">World Vision Sudan proposes to implementing the GFA, the Nutrition (eBSFP) and resilience programs, the FFA and PSN programs in 13 localities (Abu Gebieha, Abu Kashola, Al Qoz, Delami, Dilling, El Abassiya, El Reif Ashargi, Elliri, Gedir, Habila, Kadugli, Rashad, Talodi) covering more than 487,758 beneficiaries, distributing 49,800.11MT of food supplies. The Productive Safety Program is also targeting 1,345 beneficiaries. The anticipated major risk is the insecurity in some camps and the general country economic instability that might affect the security situation and impact on the implementation. To mitigate this, World Vision will work closely with the Humanitarian aid Commission (HAC), Protection Agencies, UN security actors to receive updates and respond appropriately to reduce or prevent an exposure of WFP food and assets, and to prevent the exposure of the beneficiaries.&amp;#160;</narrative>
  </description>
